[h1]Object Properties[/h1]

You can access object properties in two ways.[code format="js" ]objectName.propertyName
//or
objectName['propertyName'][/code]
This example demonstrates how to access the age of our person object. [code format="js" codeId="686"]var person = {
 name: "John", age: 31, 
 favColor: "green", height: 183
};
var x = [b]person.age;[/b]
var y = [b]person['age'];[/b][/code]
JavaScript's built-in [b]length [/b]property is used to count the number of characters in a property or string.[code format="js" codeId="687"]var course = {name: "JS", lessons: 41};
document.write(course[b].[/b]name[b].length[/b]);
//Outputs 2[/code]
